OL,4,CStars call for 'gadget levy' to fund UK
OL,5,Ccreatives
OL,6, Olivia Coleman, John Nettles and Joanne
OL,7, Harris are among dozens of high-profile
OL,8, artists calling for a portion of gadget
OL,9, sales revenue in the UK to go into a
OL,10, fund for performers and creators.
OL,12,FIn a letter in Tuesday's Times
OL,13,Fnewspaper, they claim a centralised
OL,14,F"Smart Fund" could generate up to #300m
OL,15,Fper year for the UK's creative sector.
OL,17,FThe levy would be between 1% and 3% of
OL,18,Fthe overall price of a device.
OL,20,FHowever, critics say it would amount to
OL,21,F"a new tax" on consumers.
